&lt;h2&gt;BANK OPPORTUNITY&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have some opportunities for Speech and Language Therapists with an interest in working with adults with acquired disorders to work on the bank for the SLT service. The adult community service works across Derby city and Derbyshire, we also have a Service Level Agreement to provide the service to Derby Hospitals. There are established and highly experienced SLTs working in these areas, with strong working relationships with the wider MDT. Our service is primarily delivered to adults in their settings; home, care home, local hospital and acute hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a large and dynamic Speech and Language Therapy service of around 100 staff working across all service areas in Derbyshire. We are looking for HCPC and RCSLT registered Speech and Language Therapists, with a minimum of 1 year&#39;s post grad experience and established skills in dysphagia assessment and management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be committed to delivering high quality evidence based practice, providing a high standard of patient focused care and be a strong team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Salton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SLT Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lisa.salton@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
